It can be seen that Equation (11) cannot be solved directly since F* is dependent on U. Here, an iterative numerical scheme is proposed to solve Equation (10), which is described as follows:


Solve KU0 = F, and set U = U0;

Calculate F*(Uk), (k = 0, 1, 2, …) according to Equation (5);

Solve Equation KUk + 1 = F*(Uk) and set U = U + Uk + 1(k = 0, 1, 2, …);

Repeat procedures (ii) and (iii), till |F*(Uk)|2<t0, where ||2 means 2-norm of a vector, and t0 is the specified allowable tolerance.
